Unofficial Translation by Insurance Regulator of Cambodia (IRC)

**Article 11 ..**

As the first step, before applying for certificate of local insurance company branch, the principal shall apply for principle approval to establish local general insurance company branch or local life insurance company branch by attaching the required documents as below:
- the request letter for principle approval to establish local general insurance company branch or local life insurance company branch;
- the receipt of administrative fee;
- the original document or a copy certified by notary of the decision of the board of directors
- the 5 (five) -years business plan of the branch signed by the director and has a company seal
- the documents on the structure, functions and roles of the branch signed by the director and has a company seal.

After reviewing and evaluating the above required documents, the **IRC** has the right to issue a principle approval or reject the application within 25 (twenty-five) days from the date of receipt of sufficient documents. The **IRC** provides this principle approval to the principal for registration of local branch establishment with the Ministry of Commerce and to proceed with other procedures as necessary.

**Article 12 ..**

After obtaining a principle approval to establish local general insurance company branch or life insurance company branch and has registered as local branch in accordance with the law of Kingdom of Cambodia, the principal shall apply for certificate of local general insurance company branch or local life insurance company branch by attaching the required documents as below:
- the request letter for certificate of local general insurance company branch or life insurance company branch;
- the receipt of administrative fee;
- the receipt of certificate fee;
- A copy with company seal of patent or patent tax receipt;
- the contract of leasing or title deed which legalized by local authority;
- A copy with company seal of the documents of local company branch registration at the Ministry of Commerce;
- A copy with company seal of the documents of identification and qualifications of the person to be appointed as the branch manager such as passport or ID card, a resume on work experience and study with a degree or professional certificate;
- An original or a copy certified by notary of the letter of criminal record of the branch manager.

After reviewing and evaluating the above required documents, the **IRC** has the right to issue a certificate or reject the application within 20 (twenty) days from the date of receiving sufficient documents.

